item.title: Aesopica: part 1
item.description: The stories of attributed to Aesop, called Aesop’s Fables or the Aesopica, are an ancient collection of stories that have been passed down to modern day. Of diverse origins they cover a wide variety of themes. Although originally intended for an adult audience, in later times were often used for the education of children.
